1
00:00:02,100 --> 00:00:03,590
We're...

2
00:00:05,740 --> 00:00:10,440
Fairy Tail wizards!!!

3
00:00:12,950 --> 00:00:14,290
Men...

4
00:00:14,290 --> 00:00:16,720
Nichiya-san, are they...?

5
00:00:18,800 --> 00:00:20,530
Let's go, Carla!

6
00:01:56,260 --> 00:01:57,900
Men...

7
00:01:57,900 --> 00:01:59,930
Oyoyoyoyo...

8
00:01:59,930 --> 00:02:02,910
We're gonna save everyone!

9
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:06,940
We're gonna save 'em, no matter what!

10
00:02:08,970 --> 00:02:10,430
Nichiya-san?

11
00:02:12,200 --> 00:02:16,780
Angels who have lost their 
wings... The Fallen!

12
00:02:17,340 --> 00:02:21,740
The Exceeds have been poisoned by the 
filth of Earthland and have Fallen!

13
00:02:22,300 --> 00:02:25,100
Oh, men!

14
00:02:25,880 --> 00:02:28,370
Two of the Fallen are escaping!

15
00:02:28,370 --> 00:02:30,710
Royal Guard, go forth!

16
00:02:32,990 --> 00:02:35,270
Fly! To Your Friends!

17
00:02:41,260 --> 00:02:42,660
Damn it...

18
00:02:43,130 --> 00:02:47,270
There's no way that Happy's a traitor!

19
00:02:47,270 --> 00:02:50,140
No way in hell, I say!

20
00:02:50,140 --> 00:02:52,630
You hear me?!

21
00:02:55,030 --> 00:02:56,920
Open this cell!

22
00:02:55,690 --> 00:02:57,140
Natsu-san...

23
00:02:57,500 --> 00:02:59,800
I'm gonna bust this thing wide open!

24
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:03,660
Roar of the Fire Dragon!

25
00:03:06,620 --> 00:03:08,660
It's no use, yeah...

26
00:03:10,640 --> 00:03:14,910
Edolas is so damn annoying!

27
00:03:14,910 --> 00:03:15,970
Carla...

28
00:03:24,700 --> 00:03:26,830
W-What's this?

29
00:03:27,130 --> 00:03:28,370
What happened?

30
00:03:28,780 --> 00:03:31,850
Hey! This has got to be 
some sort of joke, right?

31
00:03:33,410 --> 00:03:36,850
Oh, right... Everyone was captured.

32
00:03:38,050 --> 00:03:40,780
Natsu... Happy...

33
00:03:40,780 --> 00:03:42,890
Wendy... Carla...

34
00:03:43,280 --> 00:03:44,780
Where did everyone go?

35
00:03:45,240 --> 00:03:47,670
And hey... Let me outta these!

36
00:03:47,670 --> 00:03:49,260
Can anybody hear me?

37
00:03:49,260 --> 00:03:50,870
God, she's loud.

38
00:03:58,190 --> 00:03:59,800
What's that noise?

39
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:01,660
Maybe it's a caterpillar?

40
00:04:01,660 --> 00:04:03,550
It's obviously not that.

41
00:04:03,550 --> 00:04:06,030
Something's coming from the castle...

42
00:04:07,190 --> 00:04:08,640
Aren't those...

43
00:04:08,640 --> 00:04:11,010
Outta our way!

44
00:04:17,030 --> 00:04:19,410
It's those heroes from before!

45
00:04:20,070 --> 00:04:22,030
And... the Royal Guard?

46
00:04:22,030 --> 00:04:24,330
Hold it!

47
00:04:24,330 --> 00:04:27,030
Men!

48
00:04:29,870 --> 00:04:31,960
Men!

49
00:04:42,210 --> 00:04:43,280
Men...

50
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:47,410
I-I'm not tired, or anything...

51
00:04:47,410 --> 00:04:49,750
I'm still young!

52
00:04:50,030 --> 00:04:53,480
I must live up to the Queen's expectations!

53
00:05:13,700 --> 00:05:16,120
Carla!

54
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:18,170
Happy!

55
00:05:21,290 --> 00:05:23,770
Hold on real tight!

56
00:05:23,770 --> 00:05:24,710
Okay!

57
00:05:44,820 --> 00:05:49,380
C-Carla... Are you okay?

58
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:51,970
Somehow...

59
00:05:55,130 --> 00:05:57,160
Happy, look at that!

60
00:05:58,660 --> 00:06:00,460
That lacrima is floating!

61
00:06:00,790 --> 00:06:03,190
It's way bigger than the one 
we saw in the Royal City.

62
00:06:03,190 --> 00:06:05,290
That's everyone from Fairy Tail!

63
00:06:06,210 --> 00:06:08,380
So that's where they were...

64
00:06:09,280 --> 00:06:11,140
Which means...

65
00:06:15,430 --> 00:06:18,550
Are we on a floating island?

66
00:06:18,790 --> 00:06:21,600
If the Royal City is way down there, then...

67
00:06:22,140 --> 00:06:24,830
Basically, the situation 
would look like this.

68
00:06:25,540 --> 00:06:27,860
H-How are we going to get 
down to the Royal City?

69
00:06:29,040 --> 00:06:32,610
We can't use our Aera like we are now...

70
00:06:35,400 --> 00:06:36,680
Natsu...

71
00:06:37,650 --> 00:06:40,180
Hey, you there!

72
00:06:40,180 --> 00:06:42,970
What the heck ya think 
yer doin' on my fields?

73
00:06:42,970 --> 00:06:44,090
Shoot!

74
00:06:47,030 --> 00:06:52,500
Yer those Fallen who the Royal Guard 
're searchin' about for, yeah?

75
00:07:01,550 --> 00:07:03,080
Get outta here!

76
00:07:03,080 --> 00:07:05,390
Aye! We're sorry!

77
00:07:05,390 --> 00:07:07,160
Men!

78
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:12,120
Did that cart which ran me 
over head over this way?

79
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:15,470
Search for it, men!

80
00:07:15,470 --> 00:07:16,830
They're already after us...

81
00:07:21,670 --> 00:07:23,780
I said get outta my fields!

82
00:07:23,780 --> 00:07:26,270
Aye! We'll leave right away!

83
00:07:26,270 --> 00:07:27,970
Then come to my house!

84
00:07:32,130 --> 00:07:33,980
Where are the soldiers?

85
00:07:34,450 --> 00:07:38,110
Did you already report to them?

86
00:07:41,290 --> 00:07:43,080
I'm sorry!

87
00:07:43,080 --> 00:07:46,210
My, you're home early today, dear.

88
00:07:46,210 --> 00:07:47,140
Oh?

89
00:07:48,500 --> 00:07:49,890
Why, hello there.

90
00:07:50,180 --> 00:07:52,070
Hello.

91
00:07:52,860 --> 00:07:54,240
What's your name?

92
00:07:54,750 --> 00:07:56,840
I'm Happy.

93
00:07:56,840 --> 00:07:58,190
Carla...

94
00:07:58,440 --> 00:08:01,090
I see. What lovely names!

95
00:08:01,440 --> 00:08:03,300
Now then, please come inside.

96
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:18,130
Oh my... That sounds like 
quite a lot of trouble.

97
00:08:19,790 --> 00:08:24,230
Sir, ma'am... Thank you for sheltering us!

98
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:27,860
Eat yer food, got it?

99
00:08:27,860 --> 00:08:28,850
Aye!

100
00:08:28,850 --> 00:08:30,070
Thank you.

101
00:08:30,400 --> 00:08:35,830
My husband here doesn't really 
go with how the kingdom thinks.

102
00:08:35,830 --> 00:08:40,120
We were kicked out long ago, 
and make our lives here.

103
00:08:41,740 --> 00:08:43,600
Don't go blabbin' about that stuff!

104
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:44,970
Yes, dear.

105
00:08:44,970 --> 00:08:47,960
I see! So that's why you...

106
00:08:47,960 --> 00:08:49,780
It ain't that.

107
00:08:50,800 --> 00:08:53,570
After you eat, yer gonna help with the work!

108
00:08:54,660 --> 00:08:56,360
A-Aye!

109
00:08:57,230 --> 00:08:58,490
Put this on!

110
00:08:59,390 --> 00:09:00,750
Hurry up and eat!

111
00:09:08,130 --> 00:09:09,740
Put yer back in it!

112
00:09:09,740 --> 00:09:11,840
You call yerself a man?!

113
00:09:12,630 --> 00:09:15,830
But I've never done this before...

114
00:09:15,830 --> 00:09:17,360
No excuses!

115
00:09:18,070 --> 00:09:20,250
Do it faster! Put yer back in it!

116
00:09:20,250 --> 00:09:21,080
Aye!

117
00:09:27,550 --> 00:09:30,970
I didn't know that a hoe 
was this heavy, sir...

118
00:09:30,970 --> 00:09:32,920
I was really surprised.

119
00:09:32,920 --> 00:09:37,930
Look here, you... That's called 
the weight of life itself!

120
00:09:38,380 --> 00:09:39,810
Uh...

121
00:09:39,810 --> 00:09:42,340
He sure makes a big deal outta things...

122
00:09:42,340 --> 00:09:45,770
But if he hears me, he'll get 
mad, so I'll keep it to myself...

123
00:09:45,770 --> 00:09:48,110
I heard it all!

124
00:09:49,300 --> 00:09:51,050
I'm sorry!

125
00:09:56,890 --> 00:09:58,460
Watch closely!

126
00:09:58,460 --> 00:10:00,210
If yer a man...

127
00:10:00,880 --> 00:10:03,680
Put some back into it!

128
00:10:04,700 --> 00:10:06,030
Man?

129
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:12,300
Doin' this much is just par for the course!

130
00:10:12,300 --> 00:10:14,800
Y-You're pretty amazing, sir!

131
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:16,580
Don't just gawk at it!

132
00:10:16,580 --> 00:10:20,860
He was just gawking at it himself... 
Or did he forget already?

133
00:10:20,860 --> 00:10:24,220
But if he hears me, he'll get 
mad, so I'll keep it to myself...

134
00:10:24,220 --> 00:10:26,880
I told ya, I can hear it all!

135
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:29,480
I'm sorry!

136
00:10:32,340 --> 00:10:34,310
Oh, you're very good at this.

137
00:10:34,310 --> 00:10:35,360
It's simple.

138
00:10:35,750 --> 00:10:36,880
I'm finished.

139
00:10:36,880 --> 00:10:38,110
Thank you.

140
00:10:41,900 --> 00:10:44,130
You weak-kneed little...

141
00:10:44,550 --> 00:10:46,340
My...

142
00:10:53,770 --> 00:10:55,360
No more...

143
00:10:55,360 --> 00:10:57,300
Weakling...

144
00:10:57,300 --> 00:11:01,880
We've made some nice cold drinks! 
Why don't you rest for a bit?

145
00:11:01,880 --> 00:11:02,550
Aye!

146
00:11:03,680 --> 00:11:06,350
Don't go drinkin' before me!

147
00:11:06,350 --> 00:11:07,850
Aye!

148
00:11:27,260 --> 00:11:29,660
I'm glad they let me out of those stocks,

149
00:11:29,660 --> 00:11:32,210
but what's with this sticky stuff?

150
00:11:32,990 --> 00:11:34,450
Hello?

151
00:11:34,450 --> 00:11:36,670
I'd really appreciate you taking 
off this sticky stuff, too!

152
00:11:36,670 --> 00:11:38,700
It's not like I can escape anyway!

153
00:11:38,700 --> 00:11:39,550
Hey!

154
00:11:39,550 --> 00:11:41,560
God, she's loud...

155
00:11:41,560 --> 00:11:45,640
Are all Earthland women like this?

156
00:11:47,210 --> 00:11:50,010
I'm not sensing any magical 
power from my keys...

157
00:11:50,010 --> 00:11:54,350
As I thought, this sticky stuff 
is suppressing my magic power...

158
00:11:55,570 --> 00:11:58,570
I wonder what happened to everyone?

159
00:12:09,390 --> 00:12:13,460
Good work on your mission. Hurry 
up and take me back to the guild.

160
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:19,490
I took them to the Royal 
City, just like you asked.

161
00:12:20,250 --> 00:12:23,510
Those guys are seriously planning 
on taking on the Royal Army.

162
00:12:23,510 --> 00:12:26,210
Yeah, I know.

163
00:12:26,210 --> 00:12:29,980
So, you refill this thing's lacrima?

164
00:12:29,980 --> 00:12:31,050
I wasn't able to.

165
00:12:31,680 --> 00:12:35,110
The army has searched through the 
black market and everywhere else,

166
00:12:35,110 --> 00:12:37,410
and there isn't even a 
shard of a lacrima left.

167
00:12:37,800 --> 00:12:41,530
I think it'll be out of magic power 
about when we reach the guild.

168
00:12:42,900 --> 00:12:46,630
And yet you had me ride to 
the Royal City and back...

169
00:12:46,630 --> 00:12:47,450
Sheesh...

170
00:12:48,260 --> 00:12:51,080
We're such big softies, you and I.

171
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:56,340
Don't get all cheeky with me, bub!

172
00:12:56,340 --> 00:12:58,040
I'm sorry!

173
00:12:58,290 --> 00:13:02,380
Technique #31: Studly Bomber!

174
00:13:04,420 --> 00:13:09,730
I'm happy that he's hiding us, 
but he sure works me hard...

175
00:13:09,730 --> 00:13:11,740
Well, <i>sorry</i> for that!

176
00:13:11,740 --> 00:13:13,410
No complainin'!

177
00:13:13,410 --> 00:13:14,570
Aye!

178
00:13:14,570 --> 00:13:16,940
I figured he could hear me...

179
00:13:19,440 --> 00:13:21,800
I wonder if Natsu and the others are safe...

180
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:25,640
I really don't have time 
to be doing this stuff...

181
00:13:30,370 --> 00:13:33,400
Don't go thinkin' of other 
stuff when yer workin'!

182
00:13:33,400 --> 00:13:34,410
Aye!

183
00:13:34,410 --> 00:13:37,540
After yer done with that, 
we'll be splittin' logs!

184
00:13:38,230 --> 00:13:39,710
Aye, sir!

185
00:13:45,280 --> 00:13:49,510
You haven't smiled once since you 
came to this house, have you?

186
00:13:50,380 --> 00:13:52,840
Even though you have such a pretty face...

187
00:13:54,440 --> 00:13:56,840
I am in no mood to smile...

188
00:13:58,150 --> 00:14:00,340
You're struggling with something, yes?

189
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:04,980
It's even more important to 
smile during those times.

190
00:14:05,430 --> 00:14:06,590
But...

191
00:14:07,190 --> 00:14:10,890
True... It's not so simple, I know...

192
00:14:16,940 --> 00:14:18,430
Doing pretty good.

193
00:14:18,990 --> 00:14:20,700
Too slow!

194
00:14:20,700 --> 00:14:22,890
You call that log-splittin'?!

195
00:14:24,400 --> 00:14:26,500
F-Fast!

196
00:14:27,050 --> 00:14:31,140
Okay! I ain't gonna lose!

197
00:14:32,140 --> 00:14:34,560
Aye, sir! Aye, sir! Aye, sir!

198
00:14:35,810 --> 00:14:37,100
Aye, sir!

199
00:14:37,100 --> 00:14:38,580
I ain't losin' neither!

200
00:14:38,580 --> 00:14:40,900
How competitive are you?

201
00:14:41,320 --> 00:14:42,980
Same to ya!

202
00:14:43,390 --> 00:14:44,770
It's the last log!

203
00:14:45,530 --> 00:14:46,690
As for me...

204
00:14:46,690 --> 00:14:48,630
I'll split it first!

205
00:14:58,420 --> 00:15:00,020
This ain't funny!

206
00:15:00,020 --> 00:15:01,350
Aye!

207
00:15:01,350 --> 00:15:05,310
Well, fine. We'll leave it like this.

208
00:15:07,400 --> 00:15:09,560
S-So tired...

209
00:15:10,300 --> 00:15:11,960
Go take a bath!

210
00:15:11,960 --> 00:15:12,890
Aye!

211
00:15:18,930 --> 00:15:20,350
Carla!

212
00:15:21,220 --> 00:15:23,750
Wait, Carla!

213
00:15:25,110 --> 00:15:26,650
You fell again.

214
00:15:28,250 --> 00:15:31,960
Why won't you leave me alone?

215
00:15:31,960 --> 00:15:32,960
I...

216
00:15:32,960 --> 00:15:34,300
Because...

217
00:15:34,700 --> 00:15:38,190
Don't give me "because"... 
Go home by yourself.

218
00:15:38,190 --> 00:15:42,140
Because we're friends, right?

219
00:15:44,870 --> 00:15:46,390
Friends?

220
00:15:48,140 --> 00:15:49,450
Yeah!

221
00:15:51,950 --> 00:15:52,980
Carla!

222
00:15:55,960 --> 00:15:58,820
That bath felt incredible...

223
00:16:02,020 --> 00:16:05,780
Happy, Carla... What exactly...

224
00:16:08,900 --> 00:16:10,150
Wendy...

225
00:16:11,800 --> 00:16:13,470
Good work.

226
00:16:13,470 --> 00:16:16,540
Doesn't it feel nice here 
after taking a bath?

227
00:16:16,540 --> 00:16:18,570
Yes, very much so!

228
00:16:18,800 --> 00:16:21,720
Your names are Happy and Carla, if I recall.

229
00:16:22,030 --> 00:16:23,910
You were born on Earthland, yes?

230
00:16:24,440 --> 00:16:26,420
Who was it that named you?

231
00:16:26,880 --> 00:16:29,270
Natsu. My friend.

232
00:16:29,500 --> 00:16:32,810
The same for me... A friend...

233
00:16:33,470 --> 00:16:36,580
Those friends have been 
captured by the kingdom.

234
00:16:36,580 --> 00:16:39,050
We have to go save them!

235
00:16:39,800 --> 00:16:41,890
So, you're going to rescue humans...

236
00:16:42,350 --> 00:16:46,980
In Extalia, thinking like that is wrong, yes?

237
00:16:47,450 --> 00:16:50,750
That's not the case. I think it's wonderful.

238
00:16:52,210 --> 00:16:55,900
Being friends has nothing to do 
with being Human or Exceed...

239
00:16:56,500 --> 00:17:02,230
After all, even if we look different, the 
shape of your heart that loves others is the same.

240
00:17:02,790 --> 00:17:04,800
The shape of your heart?

241
00:17:05,280 --> 00:17:06,190
Yes...

242
00:17:06,520 --> 00:17:09,790
The shape of a loving heart 
is the same for everyone.

243
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:16,800
My heart...

244
00:17:18,100 --> 00:17:23,530
My heart isn't my own... It's being 
manipulated by someone else...

245
00:17:24,520 --> 00:17:29,840
I don't even know if the words 
I'm saying now are my own, or...

246
00:17:29,840 --> 00:17:33,730
They're your words, Carla! 
It's your heart, Carla!

247
00:17:36,060 --> 00:17:40,820
Our hearts that want to rescue 
our friends are our own!

248
00:17:41,620 --> 00:17:42,980
Happy...

249
00:17:42,980 --> 00:17:48,480
Yes, that's right. You might be a little 
lost now, but I'm sure you'll be fine.

250
00:17:48,800 --> 00:17:51,860
You have such a wonderful 
knight next to you, after all!

251
00:17:53,050 --> 00:17:54,670
Knight-sama?

252
00:17:55,630 --> 00:17:58,280
You can find your own heart.

253
00:17:58,750 --> 00:18:01,680
Or rather, it's already within you.

254
00:18:07,670 --> 00:18:10,210
All you need to do is realize that.

255
00:18:10,820 --> 00:18:14,150
Believe in the love you feel.

256
00:18:21,560 --> 00:18:25,180
Thank goodness... You finally smiled.

257
00:18:25,410 --> 00:18:27,100
You're very cute.

258
00:18:27,100 --> 00:18:28,840
You're a strange one, ma'am.

259
00:18:28,840 --> 00:18:30,190
Really?

260
00:18:30,190 --> 00:18:35,800
Because all the Exceeds think that 
they're like angels or something.

261
00:18:35,800 --> 00:18:38,150
They said that humans are an inferior race.

262
00:18:38,150 --> 00:18:42,500
Yes... I once thought like that.

263
00:18:43,510 --> 00:18:46,850
But then our children were 
taken by the Queen...

264
00:18:48,440 --> 00:18:55,860
She collected eggs... 100 children, for 
the Dragon Slayer Extermination Project.

265
00:18:56,720 --> 00:19:03,130
Then, without even seeing the faces of our 
children, they were sent to Earthland.

266
00:19:05,160 --> 00:19:10,330
We were kicked out of the kingdom 
because we opposed the project...

267
00:19:11,410 --> 00:19:12,930
It was around that time...

268
00:19:13,450 --> 00:19:16,480
We aren't gods or angels...

269
00:19:17,320 --> 00:19:21,700
We're just parents, that's all...

270
00:19:22,390 --> 00:19:23,570
That's when I realized.

271
00:19:24,590 --> 00:19:30,660
Then, it didn't matter whether one 
was an Exceed or a Human any more.

272
00:19:31,930 --> 00:19:36,370
My husband can be a bit harsh, 
but I feel the same way.

273
00:19:39,080 --> 00:19:41,860
Stop talkin' about that dumb stuff!

274
00:19:41,860 --> 00:19:43,720
How much longer are y'gonna be here?!

275
00:19:43,720 --> 00:19:44,740
Dear...

276
00:19:44,740 --> 00:19:47,050
Yer makin' such a down face!

277
00:19:47,050 --> 00:19:49,440
Just livin' is happiness!

278
00:19:50,080 --> 00:19:51,750
Don't be such a softy!

279
00:19:51,750 --> 00:19:53,920
Get outta here already!

280
00:19:54,520 --> 00:19:56,840
Dear, isn't that a bit sudden?

281
00:19:58,470 --> 00:20:00,650
You're right, sir!

282
00:20:00,650 --> 00:20:04,010
We have to go save everyone, and soon!

283
00:20:05,400 --> 00:20:06,220
Yes.

284
00:20:06,770 --> 00:20:10,400
If you stay bein' this scared, you 
couldn't do it even if you had a chance!

285
00:20:10,400 --> 00:20:13,600
Kids these days don't understand nothin'!

286
00:20:20,750 --> 00:20:24,870
Thanks, sir! Thanks, ma'am!

287
00:20:25,710 --> 00:20:27,450
Never darken my door again!

288
00:20:27,450 --> 00:20:29,370
Have a safe journey!

289
00:20:31,600 --> 00:20:36,020
Carla, did you understand what he just said?

290
00:20:36,020 --> 00:20:38,040
Yes, I understand.

291
00:20:38,040 --> 00:20:42,560
When I arrived at Edolas, 
I was filled with unease!

292
00:20:42,900 --> 00:20:44,880
Yes... As was I.

293
00:20:45,500 --> 00:20:47,800
But things are different now!

294
00:20:54,860 --> 00:20:58,810
We have to move forward! We have to fly!

295
00:21:01,290 --> 00:21:07,030
We're Exceeds... The only creatures in 
Edolas who have magic power inside them...

296
00:21:07,550 --> 00:21:11,530
The reason we couldn't use magic was 
because of the unease in our hearts!

297
00:21:18,540 --> 00:21:25,980
See? When we can see the shape of our 
hearts, wings will let us move forward!

298
00:21:26,750 --> 00:21:29,350
Let's go! We have to save everyone!

299
00:21:29,350 --> 00:21:30,350
Aye!

300
00:21:34,710 --> 00:21:36,780
Take a look a that, Marl!

301
00:21:36,780 --> 00:21:38,830
They <i>can</i> fly after all!

302
00:21:38,830 --> 00:21:42,100
He flies just like you, Lucky...

303
00:21:42,100 --> 00:21:45,640
Don't be stupid! It ain't 
just in how he <i>flies</i>...

304
00:21:46,450 --> 00:21:47,610
Right...

305
00:22:05,720 --> 00:22:08,460
Do you think that she was his girlfriend?

306
00:22:10,190 --> 00:22:14,360
Yer 100 years too young to 
be bringin' a girl home!

307
00:22:14,360 --> 00:22:17,830
He was raised to be a kind child 
who's thoughtful of his friends...

308
00:22:20,420 --> 00:22:21,940
Aye!

309
00:23:55,950 --> 00:24:00,620
I'm going to save you, Natsu! That's 
like opposite the usual pattern.

310
00:24:00,620 --> 00:24:01,450
Yeah...

311
00:24:01,450 --> 00:24:03,550
For some reason, I'm all excited though!

312
00:24:03,550 --> 00:24:06,430
It's okay to think of myself as the 
main character this time, right?

313
00:24:06,430 --> 00:24:08,170
Whatever, just come save us already!

314
00:24:08,170 --> 00:24:12,390
Oh, what's this? Are you sure you 
should be talking to me like that?

315
00:24:12,390 --> 00:24:14,100
Happy, your character's completely changed.

316
00:24:14,100 --> 00:24:16,780
Next time: Code ETD!

317
00:24:16,780 --> 00:24:20,010
That's less like being the hero, 
and more being the big evil boss!

318
00:24:20,010 --> 00:24:23,140
The big evil boss, huh? I think I like it.

319
00:24:23,140 --> 00:24:25,160
Now <i>you</i> need help...

